{
  "texts": [
    "In this sense, generative AI solutions-such as OpenAI's Chat-GPT [158,159,166]-yet would not fit into the \"hosting service providers\" since they generate content themselves rather than just storing and disseminating user-generate content.",
    "Therefore, loopholes in protections persist regarding risks from harmful AI-generated content posted publicly that cannot be fully removed once spread (Code: NTD) [78].",
    "Also, provisions take an individualized view of viral harms rather than shared duties of good-faith public discourse.",
    "The DSA rules only apply (Code: DD) to \"online platforms\" that disseminate information to the general public.",
    "Private messaging services like WhatsApp or Telegram groups are excluded."
  ]
}